  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Coming Glory of God’s House"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "On the twenty-first day of the seventh month, the word of the LORD came through Haggai the prophet, saying:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "“Speak to Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua son of Jehozadak,",
          {
            "noteId": 2353
          },
          "the high priest, and also to the remnant of the people. Ask them,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "‘Who is left among you who saw this house in its former glory? How does it look to you now? Does it not appear to you like nothing in comparison?’"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now be strong, O Zerubbabel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Be strong, O Joshua son of Jehozadak,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the high priest.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And be strong, all you people of the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Work! For I am with you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the promise I made to you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when you came out of Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And My Spirit remains among you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be afraid.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD of Hosts says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Once more, in a little while,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will shake the heavens and the earth,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2354
          },
          {
            "text": "the sea and the dry land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will shake all the nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will come with all their treasures,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will fill this house with glory,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The silver is Mine, and the gold is Mine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The latter glory of this house",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be greater than the former,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And in this place I will provide peace,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Blessings for a Defiled People"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "On the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, in the second year of Darius, the word of the LORD came to Haggai the prophet, saying,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "“This is what the LORD of Hosts says: ‘Ask the priests for a ruling."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "If a man carries consecrated meat in the fold of his garment, and it touches bread, stew, wine, oil, or any other food, does that item become holy?’”",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "“No,” replied the priests."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "So Haggai asked, “If one who is defiled by contact with a corpse touches any of these, does it become defiled?”",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "“Yes, it becomes defiled,” the priests answered."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "Then Haggai replied, “So it is with this people and this nation before Me, declares the LORD, and so it is with every work of their hands; whatever they offer there is defiled."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Now consider carefully from this day forward:",
          {
            "noteId": 2355
          },
          "Before one stone was placed on another in the temple of the LORD,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "from that time, when one came expecting a heap of twenty ephahs of grain,",
          {
            "noteId": 2356
          },
          "there were but ten. When one came to the winepress to draw out fifty baths,",
          {
            "noteId": 2357
          },
          "there were but twenty."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "I struck you—all the work of your hands—with blight, mildew, and hail, but you did not turn to Me, declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Consider carefully from this day forward—from the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, the day the foundation of the LORD’s temple was laid—consider carefully:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "Is there still seed in the barn? The vine, the fig, the pomegranate, and the olive tree have not yet yielded fruit. But from this day on, I will bless you.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Zerubbabel the LORD’s Signet Ring"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "For the second time that day, the twenty-fourth day of the month, the word of the LORD came to Haggai, saying,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "“Tell Zerubbabel governor of Judah that I am about to shake the heavens and the earth:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will overturn royal thrones",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and destroy the power",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "of the kingdoms of the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will overturn chariots and their riders;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "horses and their riders will fall,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "each by the sword of his brother.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will take you, My servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will make you like My signet ring,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for I have chosen you,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
